cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a method for learning personalized predictive models of non-stationary, transient, and time-heterogeneous user trajectories. This involves dealing with challenges such as hidden networks, website links, and geographic location. The paper also mentions next product recommendation, next song recommendation, next location prediction, and general arbitrary-length user trajectory prediction. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other possible sub-categories include cs.SD (Sound) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
